            "comment": "Details the function and focus of the research labs at Lythora Station",
            "content": "Lythora Station features several specialized labs, each designed to focus on a specific area of research. The Ecology Lab studies the interactions between Lythora’s species and their environments, while the Marine Lab conducts oceanic research. The Climatology Lab monitors weather patterns and atmospheric conditions, and the Geology Lab, partly underground, investigates the planet’s tectonic activity and magnetic anomalies. These labs are equipped with state-of-the-art tools and are partially automated, allowing LYRA and a minimal human crew to efficiently conduct in-depth research.",
