            "comment": "Details on the accommodations and amenities for the crew",
            "content": "The living quarters at Lythora Station are compact and functional, designed to support the small human crew assigned to the outpost. Each crew member has a private cabin with essential amenities, and there is a shared galley and recreation area. Despite the station’s automated nature, human presence is still crucial, and the quarters are designed to maintain comfort and morale during long assignments. The quarters also include a small med bay and exercise area to ensure the crew’s health and well-being.",
