            "comment": "Explains the role of robotics and automation in station operations",
            "content": "Lythora Station is heavily automated, relying on a fleet of drones and robots to conduct fieldwork, maintenance, and data collection. Aerial drones scout and map the terrain, aquatic drones explore the oceans, and ground robots handle tasks like sample collection and environmental monitoring. Android assistants within the station support human researchers by performing delicate tasks in the labs. Maintenance bots ensure the station’s systems remain operational, even in the harsh conditions of Lythora.",
