            "comment": "Details the station’s power sources and sustainability efforts",
            "content": "Lythora Station is powered primarily by geothermal energy, harnessed from the planet’s tectonic activity. Supplementary power comes from solar arrays that capture energy from Tharos’s light. The station is designed for long-term sustainability, with systems in place for water desalination, ice harvesting, and waste recycling. A closed-loop recycling system converts waste into usable resources, minimizing the need for resupply from off-world. The greenhouse and hydroponic systems provide fresh food and serve as research facilities for studying Lythora’s plant life.",
