            "comment": "Details on the smaller, unmanned outposts supporting Lythora Station",
            "content": "In addition to the main base, Lythora Station operates several unmanned satellite outposts positioned across the planet. These outposts include a polar research station, a deep-sea observatory, and a high-altitude weather station. Each outpost is largely automated, with drones and robots conducting the majority of the research and maintenance tasks. Data from these outposts is transmitted back to the main base, where LYRA processes and integrates it into the station’s ongoing research efforts.",
